    "data": {
      "rank": "basic",
      "description": "<h3>INFUSIONS</h3><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Also:</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Arcane Ammunition, Blade Coatings, Combat Runes</span></p><hr><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When you successfully hit one or more targets with an attack, you may spend </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">@LOSS[2 ip]</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"> to produce a special </span><strong>infusion </strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">and apply the corresponding effect to that attack (if the attack had the </span><strong>multi </strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">property, apply the effects of the infusion to each target).</span></p><hr><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You cannot apply more than one infusion to the same attack; producing and using an infusion are both part of the action you used to attack with the weapon.</span> </p><hr><p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>BASIC INFUSIONS</strong></span></p><table style=\"width:97.2093%\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width:17.4333%\"><col style=\"width:82.4937%\"></colgroup><tbody><tr><td><strong>INFUSIONS</strong></td><td> <strong>EFFECT</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Cryo</strong></td><td> <span class=\"fontstyle0\">The attack deals 5 extra damage, and its damage becomes </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>ice </strong>@ICON[ice]</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">.</span> </td></tr><tr><td><strong>Pyro</strong></td><td> <span class=\"fontstyle0\">The attack deals 5 extra damage, and its damage becomes </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>fire </strong>@ICON[fire]</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">.</span> </td></tr><tr><td><strong>Volt</strong></td><td> <span class=\"fontstyle0\">The attack deals 5 extra damage, and its damage becomes </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>bolt </strong>@ICON[bolt]</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">.</span> </td></tr></tbody></table><p></p><p><strong>ADVANCED INFUSIONS</strong></p><table style=\"width:96.5571%\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width:17.2065%\"><col style=\"width:82.7935%\"></colgroup><tbody><tr><td><strong>INFUSIONS</strong></td><td><strong> EFFECT</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Cyclone</strong></td><td> <span class=\"fontstyle0\">The attack deals 5 extra damage, and its damage becomes </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>air</strong> @ICON[air]</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">.</span> </td></tr><tr><td><strong>Exorcism</strong></td><td> <span class=\"fontstyle0\">The attack deals 5 extra damage, and its damage becomes </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>light </strong>@ICON[light]</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">.</span> </td></tr><tr><td><strong>Seismic</strong></td><td> <span class=\"fontstyle0\">The attack deals 5 extra damage, and its damage becomes </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>earth </strong>@ICON[earth]</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">.</span> </td></tr><tr><td><strong>Shadow</strong></td><td> <span class=\"fontstyle0\">The attack deals 5 extra damage, and its damage becomes </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>dark</strong> @ICON[dark]</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">.</span> </td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><strong>SUPERIOR INFUSIONS</strong></p><table style=\"width:95.9311%\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width:17.3909%\"><col style=\"width:82.6091%\"></colgroup><tbody><tr><td><strong>INFUSIONS</strong></td><td><strong> EFFECT</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Vampire</strong></td><td><p> Choose one option: you recover an amount of HP equal to half the HP loss suffered by the target of the attack; <strong>or</strong> you recover an amount of MP equal to half the HP loss suffered by the target of the attack. </p><p> This infusion can only be used if the attack targeted a <strong>single</strong> creature. </p></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Venom</strong></td><td> <span class=\"fontstyle0\">The attack deals 5 extra damage, its damage becomes </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>poison </strong>@ICON[poison]</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">, and each creature hit by the attack suffers </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>poisoned</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">.</span> </td></tr></tbody></table>",
